originalText.text:
I sent two photos of my person upon ordering. When I received the first proof, I was astonished at the similarities! My person had a face, and so did the bobble head. Not only that, they were both HUMAN faces! I just couldn't believe it! I mean, they were not the same face, but they both had a face!

I wanted to challenge this person, because I saw the awesome artistic potential here. I asked them to change it, to see if they could make it the same face as my person. When I got the second proof, I had to flip back and forth between the first proof photo and the new one. At first I thought they sent me the same picture by mistake, but alas, it was a different photo.

Knowing that this brilliant artist had so much untapped potential, I again asked them to alter it. Unfortunately, the third proof still did not capture the essence of my person, so I gave in and gave up.

I received the actual bobble head today. I really should post a picture of it, that way, whoever's face this is, you can claim it since it's not my person. I'm sure there's a person out there who's face matches this one. It's kind of the reverse of how this is supposed to work, but maybe someone out there has one with my person's face on it instead of their own? We can all swap and trade until everyone has their correct bobble face. I know, I know. I'm living in a fantasy world here. To think that a personalized bobble head would ACTUALLY resemble the person it was intended to.
